Formula to create a working salt environment in Qubes for development
and testing. Qubes will be created for salt-master and minion,
preconfigured to allow for salting.  It will be necessary to copy the
key fingerprint from salt-master to the minion, as described here:
https://docs.saltproject.io/en/latest/ref/configuration/index.html#master-key-fingerprint

It should be enough to copy the salt directory to /srv/salt in dom0,
and then, as root:
qubesctl top enable salt.source
qubesctl --show-output --targets=template-salt,salt-master,minion state.apply

qubesctl will process in this order - dom0,templates,qubes - so everything
should be automagically processed in the correct order.

If multiple minions are required, clone the minion. Start the new qube,
and stop the salt-minion service. Edit the file `/etc/salt/minion_id`
to show the new id. Remove the old keys, and generate new keys. Restart
the service and the new keys should be available to be accepted in the
salt-master.
If the new minion is called minion2, then run on minion2:
```
systemctl stop salt-minion
vi /etc/salt/minion_id
rm -rf /etc/salt/pki/minion/minion*
salt-key -u root --gen-keys=minion2
systemctl start salt-minion
```

The new domain is offline. If network access is required, then set a
netvm in salt-master.
